  "Prerequisites": "A basic familiarity with food service or hospitality operations, along with a general awareness of common dietary requirements such as allergies and intolerances, is all that is needed to get started with this course.",
  "Learning objectives": "By the end of this course, you will be able to identify the key risks associated with AI-generated menus and food recommendations, particularly in relation to dietary restrictions and allergens. You will also be able to apply practical strategies to verify and communicate allergen information accurately, ensuring the safety and wellbeing of guests across hospitality and food service settings.",
  "lessons": [
    {
      "lesson title": "AI-Generated Menus and Recommendations",
      "order": 1,
      "Description": "This lesson explores how artificial intelligence is increasingly being used to generate menus and food recommendations in hospitality and catering settings. While AI tools can offer exciting possibilities for personalisation and efficiency, they also introduce significant risks when it comes to dietary restrictions and allergens. You will learn how AI-generated content can sometimes produce inaccurate or incomplete information about ingredients, which could put customers with allergies or specific dietary needs in danger. The lesson will help you identify common pitfalls, understand your responsibilities as a food service professional, and develop practical strategies for verifying AI-generated recommendations before they reach your customers. By the end, you will feel more confident in using AI tools safely and responsibly within your workplace.",
      "status": "draft",
